<p>I quite often use a formula like:</p>  <pre><code>=1*(A2=G2) </code></pre>  <p>If A2 and G2 are the same then it returns <code>1</code> - otherwise it returns <code>0</code>.</p>  <p>I realise it is trivial with an <code>IF</code> function but I'm <em>specifically</em> interested in this format of function using <code>1*</code>.  </p>  <p>How can I amend it so that if A2 and G2 are NOT the same it returns <code>1</code>, otherwise <code>0</code>?</p>